\over2}}$ velocity perturbation, which is a generalization of\nTheorem 1 in [22] but the construction is more difficult due to the $\\beta$'s\nterm. Finally, we prove nonlinear inviscid damping for Couette flow in some\nGevrey spaces by extending the method of [4] to the $\\beta$-plane equation on\n$\\mathbb{T}\\times\\mathbb{R}$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 11 Feb 2022 15:43:04 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-02-14"}
